      <h2>About</h2>
      <p>This ongoing project focuses on the rise and decline of a soft-erotic cinema in Ghent. The case study is contextualized by the Ghent Cinema City project, but relies on the unique business archive of the managers family Bonnevalle to study the financial background, the programming trends, and the entanglements with the police, the justice department and the city. Based on a clear historical understanding of the place, the research is enhanced with programming research based on the newspaper advertisements and oral histories on cinemagoing in the famous ‘Leopolleke’ of Ghent.</p>
